cargo_inventory.name: Jerry Cans
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Just good ol', classic jerry cans. Not very space efficient, but small and convenient.

cargo_inventory.name: Water Jerry Cans
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Just good ol', classic jerry cans. Not very space efficient, but small and convenient. Painted blue, so that nobody accidentally puts fuel in this potable water container.

cargo_inventory.name: Water Drums
cargo_inventory.base_desc: A 55 gallon drum of water. Capped with a resealable spout, so the water can be safely managed. Painted blue, so that nobody accidentally puts fuel in this potable water container.

cargo_inventory.name: Argon Tanks
cargo_inventory.base_desc: 4 tanks of argon, an inert gas; useful as shielding gas during welding or certain advanced manufacturing techniques. Lashed to a heavy duty, fenced pallet for easier transport.

cargo_inventory.name: Aerogel
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Aerogel is one of the lightest known solids; composed of silica nanoparticles, this material is an extremely effective insulator, and nearly weightless.

cargo_inventory.name: Sculptures
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Handcrafted sculptures made from sustainable materials, representing the artistic renaissance of the post-collapse era.

cargo_inventory.name: Beer Kegs
cargo_inventory.base_desc: 50-liter kegs of locally brewed beer, a post-collapse luxury that helps maintain morale.

cargo_inventory.name: Algae Cultivation Tanks
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Self-contained bioreactors for growing high-protein algae strains. Includes filtration and harvesting systems for continuous production.

cargo_inventory.name: MRE Boxes
cargo_inventory.base_desc: 12 pack of shitty, pre-collapse MREs. Absolutely disgusting, but they function as food. Barely.

cargo_inventory.name: Mail
cargo_inventory.base_desc:
Sorted batches of letters, packages, and important documents requiring secure transport between settlements.

"Call us 'The Horsepower Express', hmm"

cargo_inventory.name: Lowering Springs
cargo_inventory.base_desc:
A set of lowering springs designed to lower a vehicle's ride height. This modification slightly enhances high-speed stability, but compromises off-road performance.

"The fitment is so clean..."

cargo_inventory.name: Airbag Spring Kit
cargo_inventory.base_desc:
An adjustable airbag spring system that allows for customizable ride height for different situations. This setup enhances handling and stability while providing excellent a plush ride over various terrains.

"Psh, bagged all the way brah. Static's for poors."

cargo_inventory.name: Järnmärke D12 inline-6 Crate Engine
cargo_inventory.base_desc: The Järnmärke D12 is a 12.1-liter inline-six diesel engine featuring a 24-valve overhead camshaft design and electronic unit injectors for precise fuel delivery. Known for its robust torque curve and fuel efficiency, it offers smooth operation and exceptional reliability for heavy-duty applications.

cargo_inventory.name: Heavy-duty Motor Driven Axles Kit
cargo_inventory.base_desc: A single motor drivetrain which can power all of the axles of a vehicle.

cargo_inventory.name: 3D-printed body panel Kit
cargo_inventory.base_desc: The nessisary thermoplastics to create a custom set of body panels for a vehicle. While these are fairly unremarkable from a functionality standpoint, they are a signifigantly cheaper and lighter option than the usual steel used for the outer shell of most vehicles.

cargo_inventory.name: Off-Road Bumpers
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Reinforced off-road bumpers designed to protect the vehicle from impacts and rough terrain. Built with heavy-duty materials, these bumpers improve durability, enhance approach and departure angles, and offer additional mounting points for recovery gear and lights.

vehicle_inventory.name: Ember
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: A tiny hatchback by American standards, this little car won't turn any heads, go very quickly, or tackle signifigant terrain, but at least it gets good gas milage.

vehicle_inventory.name: Bloom
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: One of the first mass market EVs, this quirky hatchback represented the vanguard of electrification.

vehicle_inventory.name: BoRS
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: The bigger, AWD sibling of Wayne's Partido ST, this large hatch features an upgraded version of the engine found in the 4 banger Stallion. Early production was marred by head gaskets which lacked some of the correct coolant passages, but this example was produced after that blunder.

vehicle_inventory.name: Y38
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: This lengthy sedan would be well suited to operate as a private limosine on the autobahn, if it weren't over half a century old.

vehicle_inventory.name: Voyage
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: This top-trim minivan features several amenities that are essential to transporting families; 15 cupholders, 4 USB ports, and even a ceiling-mounted screen, which can either play movies off disks, or even accept a HDMI input, with sound through the car's main sound system, or a set of wireless headphones.

vehicle_inventory.name: Caballo
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: A spiritual cousin of the Stallion, this Rove competitor was one of the first Sport Utility Vehicles that was primarily marketed towards civilian, domestic usage, aided by the inclusion of a removable hardtop roof.

vehicle_inventory.name: Caballo Strix
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: After Wayne brought back their cult classic Caballo nameplate, there was much clamoring to see a similar "Strix" trim level as was seen in the W-150 and Dragoon pickups. A few years into the new production run, Wayne gave the desert racers what they were asking for, and these trucks could be seen at parking malls everywhere before the collapse.

vehicle_inventory.name: Rapid
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: This was from a rental company, and is beat to hell. Still, it has an enourmous cargo capacity compared to any other light truck.
